## Description
- the First Dragon in existence
- THE Ancient Red Dragon
- leader of The [[Chromatic Dragons|Chromatic Dragons]]
- creator of [[2. Mysteries/Cyzste Zimno|Cyzste Zimno]]

## Notes
- first told of by Ambesh on a full moon - [[6. Inbox - Session Notes/2022-09-25|2022-09-25]]
- born of The[[ Holy Light| Holy Light]]
- often conflated with The Holy Light
- stood against the flames, controlling and bending them to it's own will
- became The Betrayer for beating back [[Ymearlis|Ymearlis]]
	- possibly the catalyst for the [[Metallic & Chromatic Dragon Wars|Metallic & Chromatic Dragon Wars]]
- said to have been [[4. World/Historical Documents/Fable of Ashardalon's Fall, The|struck down by his own fabled longsword]] - [[2. Mysteries/Marigold Moon's Research#Fable of Ashardalon's Fall|Marigold Moon's Research#Fable of Ashardalon's Fall]]

## Direct Historical References
### Fable of Ashardalon's Fall

<div class="transclusion internal-embed is-loaded"><div class="markdown-embed">

<div class="markdown-embed-title">



</div>

Many believe it was the might of The [[Closed Eye|Closed Eye]] that tipped the scales of the war. Though The [[Confluence|Confluence]] and Closed Eye are attributed to quelling many Chromatic Adversaries, one such enemy stood. A blinding light to the Eye, the barrier to the Confluence: [[Ashardalon|Ashardalon]].

A wrath-fueled dragon of bloody scales, who crushed mountains and lifted oceans, Ashardalon knew no mercy for the Material. The air boiled and seas quivered from their gaze. Men melted and rock split from their breath. Even now, to utter their name would be to welcome [[Ignacious|Ignacious]] into one's heart.

---

When the Closed Eye began to descend, a select few sought other means of salvation. Following the [[Holy Light|Holy Light]], their journey brought them to the source. Many souls were lost in the finding of The Light, but it was with the ascension that they learned of the Material's sanctuary.

With captain given to the Light, all but stood left was [[2. Mysteries/Cyzste Zimno|Cyzste Zimno]] and their cold-steel blade. With swipe and parry, the valiant Cyzste defended against Ashardalon to avenge ascended squad. The plates o the world shifted with Ashardalon's rage, held back by hilt of Light's creation. Ultimately, Cyzste gave their last breath to plunge their blade deep within Ashardalon's heart. The flame had been quelled. The mountains shook no longer. The had no cause for boiling.
